<title>BRIEF-Damaged Enbridge pipe to run at reduced pressure</title>
<source>Reuters</source>
<date>2010-08-06</date>
<snippet>... Executive Pat Daniel and Steve Wuori, president of Enbridge's liquids pipeline division, at a news conference on the company's oil pipeline rupture and spill: ...</snippet>
<content>
        
    
Aug 6 (Reuters) - Enbridge Inc (ENB.TO) Chief Executive Pat
Daniel and Steve Wuori, president of Enbridge's liquids
pipeline division, at a news conference on the company's oil
pipeline rupture and spill:

 * Enbridge CEO says expects to run Michigan line at reduced
pressure on restart * Exec says has no timeline for oil pipeline
restart * Exec says it is possible section of replacement pipe
could be in place this weekend * CEO says no estimate yet of financial impact on Enbridge
from pipeline break
 (Reporting by Jeffrey Jones)




